HEADWORD: Entomology
<hw>En`to*mol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Entomologies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'e`ntomon</grk> insect (so called because nearly cut in two, fr.
<grk>'e`ntomos</grk> cut in; <grk>'en</grk> in + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to
cut) + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>entomologie</ets>. See <er>In</er>,
and <er>Tome</er>, and cf. <er>Insect</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
part of zo⟦oum⟧logy which treats of insects.</def>⟦br⟧
